# Pre-filled pull request open links

When the user (or workflow) needs a **one-click GitHub link** that opens **Create pull request** with the description **already correct**, do not rely on `https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/pull/new/<branch>` alone. That path only loads the empty web template; the user still has to type everything.

## Required link shape

Use GitHub’s **compare** URL with `quick_pull=1`, `title`, and `body` (see [Using query parameters to create a pull request](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/proposing-changes-to-your-work-with-pull-requests/using-query-parameters-to-create-a-pull-request)):

```text
https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>/compare/dev...<head-branch>?quick_pull=1&title=<url-encoded-title>&body=<url-encoded-body>
```

- **Base branch:** `dev` (integration branch for this repo — see `CONTRIBUTING.md`).
- **`title`:** Short PR title (aligned with commit subject / change scope).
- **`body`:** The **entire** PR description in one string, then URL-encoded.

## Body content (non-negotiable)

The `body` query parameter **replaces** the default pull request template in the form; it does **not** merge with `.github/pull_request_template.md`. Therefore the encoded `body` MUST already contain the **full** structure and headings from `.github/pull_request_template.md`, with **every section filled** for this PR:

- **Summary** — what changed and why (concrete bullets).
- **Scope** — explicit in scope / out of scope.
- **Risk and Rollback** — regression risk + rollback plan (or “low / revert this PR”).
- **Verification** — checkbox, commands run, results (for docs-only: state CI path filters / `not run` honestly).
- **Docs Impact** — check the right box; list touched docs if any.
- **Checklist** — reflect reality (checked only if true).

Write the body in **English** (same as committed `docs/` prose).

## Encoding

Use proper URL encoding for `title` and `body` (e.g. newlines → `%0A`, spaces → `%20` or `+`). If a tool/script generates the link, use standard percent-encoding (equivalent to `encodeURIComponent` for UTF-8, then encode `'` as needed for URLs).

## Long bodies and limits

If the full URL would be unwieldy or risks **414 URI Too Long**, give the user:

1. A short compare link: `.../compare/dev...<branch>?quick_pull=1&title=...` (title only), and  
2. The full PR body as a **markdown code block** to paste into the description field, **or**  
3. The equivalent `gh pr create` / `--body-file` command.

## After `git push`

When sharing “open PR” instructions after a push to a task branch, **prefer the pre-filled compare URL** (or body-in-chat fallback above) over a bare `/pull/new/...` link.

Canonical team doc: `CONTRIBUTING.md` (Branch and PR workflow + pre-filled links).
